Here’s why you ️should ALWAYS lynch on day 1 . Now, while this will usually end up with a vanillatownie down, this is incredibly useful. First off, the prospect of a lynch fuels discussion to a great degree. When there’s an actual vote ️ happening, it’s a motivator to talk and for discussion to be more productive , while people usually don’t care much about no lynch days. Also, the flip on the player lynched is incredibly useful down the line ‍♀️ . We can deduce scum based on their behaviour relative to the flip and using vote ️ reading, which is impossible ❌ without lynching someone. Something else to be considered is that town ️ is playing against the clock . If scum aren’t dead by a certain point, they lose . Therefore, they must take the most advantage of their time ⏲️, which would involve lynching for the reasons listed above. To note is that although scum will usually not be lynched D1, it can happen, and if it does, town ️ basically wins the game right there. Lynching leads to the best outcomes .
